"a.(声音)沙哑的，粗糙的 【英】 adj.(声音)沙哑的， 粗糙的(disagreeably harsh or strident; hoarse) 【记】 rauc(=hoarse 沙哑的)＋ous 【例】 Her voice is rather raucous. dj. 沙哑的(声音粗重, 低沉的) 【记】读: 我咳嗽－沙哑的 【反】melodious(adj 音调优美的) 【记】音：热，嚷渴死→热得，嚷得喉咙干渴→沙哑；音：嚷咳嗽，嗓子咳嗽后嘶哑的声音 【相关】hoarse (音：吼嘶)嘶哑的 raucous (adj.)  1769, from Latin raucus ""hoarse"" (also source of French rauque, Spanish ronco, Italian rauco), related to ravus ""hoarse,"" from PIE echoic base *reu- ""make hoarse cries"" (cognates: Sanskrit rayati ""barks,"" ravati ""roars;"" Greek oryesthai ""to howl, roar;"" Latin racco ""a roar;"" Old Church Slavonic rjevo ""I roar;"" Lithuanian rekti ""roar;"" Old English rarian ""to wail, bellow""). Middle English had rauc in the same sense, from the same source."
